node.text:
This Halloween we decided to throw a Hocus Pocus themed family party at home, and watch the movie now available on Digital in 4K Ultra HD. October is going to be a crazy month for us! We’ll be packing up and moving to Nashville but I’m not sure if we’ll make it in time for Halloween. So instead, we decided to celebrate Halloween at home, before the move, and the kids LOVED IT! #ad 
.
.
We made Spellbook Brownies, Mummy Dogs, Dead Mans Toes, Life Potion, and Amuck-Amuck-AMUNCH (watch the video for how-to’s). Combine that with a fog machine, trick-or-treating around the house, and a Hocus Pocus movie night and you’ve got yourself a Halloween Party! We watch the beloved classic Hocus Pocus every year but this year it was crystal clear on the big screen in 4K Ultra HD and it always serves as the BEST kickoff to our holiday season. 
.
.
What are your plans for Halloween?
@disney #hocuspocus

node.text: We had ZERO plans but we did it! We made the bunk room of OUR dreams. ✨ Oh, and the kids like it too. 😂👌🏻 What are some questions you have about the space? If it’s about the DIY I’ll grab Brad (maybe I can even get him to do a live q&a) if it’s about the decor I’M ALL EARS. 👂🏻👂🏻Thanks for being here with us for another fun project, friends! 👐🏻 Now onto the next!

node.text: Time for a little Master Bedroom Room Refresh with HomeDepot.com/decor! Fresh linens, cute throw blankets, new greenery, nightstands, and rug…loving the calm, airy vibe in here. 🌿 Oh, and can we talk about those new yummy leather benches at the end of the bed?? I’ve got all of the products linked on the blog (link in profile). @homedepot #homedepotpartner

node.text: You might not believe it, but we got ALL the items we needed for a room refresh from The Home Depot! It’s more than just tools, guys! The beds, bedding, throw pillows, desk, leather chair, book holder, wall art, rug, plants and planter—all came from their website. The selection will blow your mind. 🤯 #HomeDepotPartner @homedepot

node.text:
The ceiling treatment is DONE!! {swipe for before} It adds so much character to the entire space. 🙌🏻✨ Y’all are troopers for following along on this one. Turns out making the faux beams was the easiest part of the whole thing. 😆🤭 If we didn’t convince you to shiplap the ceiling, did we at least convince you to add faux beams SOMEWHERE in your house? 
.
.
And just wanted to say a BIG huge THANK YOU for following along on our DIY adventures these past 58 months. Holy cow…we’ve been doing this 58 months. 🤭 We are taking the next month off IG to be with our kids for the second half of summer and to finish building out our first brick + mortar @urbansips in Franklin. We’ll see y’all in August, FAUX FAM! We’ll miss you!! #diy #diyprojects

node.text: Visited the first house we ever owned today. We bought this rambler almost 16 years ago and brought Chase home from the hospital to this house. This is also the house that Brad scraped asbestos off the ceilings (WITHOUT a mask…of course 🤭). This home, just shy of 80 years old, gave us our start. Our first set of DIY projects, our first baby, our first taste of making a house OUR HOME…and it we loved it. Thanks cute 1943 rambler in Provo, Utah. You’ll always be our first baby #fauxfarmhouse. 🏡

node.text: By a show of hands (er, heart taps 📲❤️)…how many of y’all wanna learn how to do  this super cool ceiling treatment?? TAP THAT HEART if you do! We usually stick to walls but this time we’re going all the way up!! This involves making some faux beams (which we haven’t done in a couple years) but we’re excited to show you how! *spoiler alert* They’re SO simple to make. 😉

node.text: Did you hear the news? Our old  #fauxfarmhouse went back on the market this past week. So many emotions! Excited for the owners we previously sold to (work is taking them away from Austin) but still feeling so attached to that house! I asked Brad if we could buy it back…he said no. 🥲 It’s already under contract but scrolling through old pics reminded me of all the work we put into that house. We left no stone unturned…no wall un-touched. Every room, every feature wall, every project—DIY’d by us. 🔨 SO many of you found us while we were customizing that home. I will forever be grateful for that home and all of the opportunities it brought us. It will always be our baby. 🤍🏡 {scroll to remember}

node.text: Welp. Today was one of the scariest days of our lives. Shortly after I shared that boomerang of Brad, @betsymikesell and I sitting safely on the beach — Brad, @taramabry and @itsmabry went for a swim on Seacrest Beach. The water was beautiful. They didn’t know it, but there was a strong riptide that swept them up and carried them out into the ocean. We didn’t know they were struggling to make it back in until we saw Tara waving her arms yelling “GET HELP!” Brad and Mark were caught and exhausted from fighting the current. 🌊 There’s so much more to this story...BUT thankfully, and against all odds, they made it back to shore and they are ALIVE. And we couldn’t be more grateful. Hold your people tight. You just never know. 🤍 Tonight I’m grateful. Grateful those three in the last pic are alive. Grateful they still have work to do here. Grateful we get a little more time with them. #justgrateful
